# Approval And Rework

## Approval mode
- Every board item has an **Approval Mode**: `HUMAN_REQUIRED` or `AUTO_APPROVE_ALLOWED`. It must be visible on the board or in the artifact; do not assume it.
- **HUMAN_REQUIRED:** After a passing review, recommend `READY_FOR_HUMAN_APPROVAL` only. Do **not** recommend `APPROVED` until a human has approved. No automation or agent output may set status to `APPROVED` for such items without explicit human approval evidence.
- **AUTO_APPROVE_ALLOWED:** After a passing review (scores and thresholds met), you may recommend direct `APPROVED`. The setting must be explicitly recorded; do not assume auto-approval. Governance still requires that review quality and evidence are documented.

## Milestone human gates
- A **milestone human gate** (e.g. "UI readiness reviewed before backend continues") blocks downstream work until that checkpoint is approved. Do not recommend or record backend (or other downstream) pickup as unblocked if the gate is not yet approved.
- Record milestone gates in **board Notes** or in the **implementation plan** so agents and humans can see the dependency. When suggesting next-task pickup or promotion, check gates first and state explicitly when work is blocked (e.g. "Backend work blocked until UI-001 is APPROVED").

## Human rejection and rework
- If a **human reviewer rejected** an item with comments:
  - Set or keep the item in `CHANGES_REQUESTED`. Do not leave it in `READY_FOR_HUMAN_APPROVAL` or move it to `APPROVED`.
  - Treat the comments as **required rework inputs** for the next agent pass. Every comment must be addressed in the artifact or explicitly deferred with rationale.
  - Update the **current artifact** to fully address the comments; do not only acknowledge them.
  - If the comments **invalidate upstream assumptions**, update the **affected requirements, plan, or dependency notes** before the item returns to review. Do not only patch the immediate artifact; list and update all affected artifacts. When recommending a board update after rejection, list which upstream artifacts must be revised.
  - After rework, the item remains in `CHANGES_REQUESTED` until a **new review pass** is run. Do not self-approve or recommend `READY_FOR_HUMAN_APPROVAL` or `APPROVED` from the same run that performed the rework; only a review pass or human can promote after rework.

